    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I'm on the middle of developing this feature. It's quite huge as it increase the complexity of the search state because of the need to introduce an \"indices\" namespace. \r\n\r\nI also encounter some edge cases and want to give you a little update on the api I'm implementing. \r\n\r\n```js\r\n <InstantSearch\r\n    appId=\"\"\r\n    apiKey=\"\"\r\n    indexName=\"first\">\r\n    <CurrentRefinements /> // widgets that are here are parameters that will be shared among every indices. \r\n    <MultiIndexContext indexName=\"first\">\r\n      <RefinementList attributeName=\"category\" /> // widgets that are here only target first\r\n      <CustomHits />\r\n      <Configure hitsPerPage={1} />\r\n      <SortBy/>\r\n    </MultiIndexContext>\r\n    <MultiIndexContext indexName=\"second\"> \r\n      <Configure hitsPerPage={1}/> //widgets that are here only target second\r\n      <RefinementList attributeName=\"categories\" />\r\n      <CustomHits />\r\n      <SortBy/>\r\n    </MultiIndexContext>\r\n<InstantSearch/>\r\n```\r\n\r\nLet me know what you think about it. ",
    "created_at": "2017-02-20T11:02:59Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1962#issuecomment-281050413",
    "id": 281050413,
